Another police headquarters has been attacked and two policemen killed as the facility was set ablaze .
The latest attack followed that of Anambra and Abia on Monday.
The Wednesday incident happened around 2 am, and the target was the Divisional Police Headquarters, Adani, in Uzo-Uwani Local Government Area of Enugu.
According to report, the unidentified gunmen killed two officers and injured others.
The intention of the attackers is not known yet.
That has been the pattern since hoodlums the police authorities claim are IPOB members have been attacking police headquarters in the southeast since April 1.
Police also said the attackers usually make advances to the headquarters armoury.
